g=A.ag("Pseudobulbar Affect Is NOT Depression",'Pseudobulbar affect (PBA, formerly "emotional lability" or "pathological crying/laughing") is an involuntary emotional display that is DISPROPORTIONATE or INCONGRUENT to the patient\'s internal emotional state. The patient may cry uncontrollably without feeling sad, or laugh at inappropriate times. It results from bilateral disruption of corticobulbar pathways. Treatment: dextromethorphan/quinidine (Nuedexta) is FDA-approved. SSRIs are also effective. This is distinct from depression.')
