m=A.ag("Board Pearl: TEE vs TTE","TEE is SUPERIOR to TTE for detecting: left atrial appendage (LAA) thrombus, patent foramen ovale (PFO), small valvular vegetations, and aortic arch atheromas. TTE is the initial screening study, but TEE should be pursued when cardioembolism is strongly suspected and TTE is unrevealing -- especially in young patients with cryptogenic stroke.")
