o=A.ag("Basmajian Principle",'Basmajian demonstrated that the supraspinatus and posterior deltoid are the primary muscles preventing inferior subluxation of the glenohumeral joint through their vertical force vector (the "locking mechanism"). In the flaccid stage, loss of supraspinatus and deltoid tone allows inferior subluxation. The joint capsule and superior capsular ligaments are secondary restraints. Subluxation itself does NOT necessarily correlate with pain severity.')
