f=A.ag("Board Pearl: ACA vs MCA Pattern","The key to differentiating ACA from MCA stroke is the distribution of weakness. ACA = leg > arm/face. MCA = face/arm > leg. If the exam describes a stroke with leg-predominant weakness plus urinary incontinence and gait apraxia, the answer is ACA. The triad of leg weakness + incontinence + gait apraxia is classic ACA.")
