q=A.aS("Brainstem Stroke Syndromes")
d=A.b2('Brainstem strokes produce characteristic "crossed" or "alternating" findings: ipsilateral cranial nerve deficits with contralateral long tract signs (motor and sensory). This pattern occurs because the cranial nerve nuclei are at the level of the lesion, while the descending/ascending tracts cross at the medullary pyramids below.',!0)
e=A.ag("Board Pearl: Crossed Findings = Brainstem",'Ipsilateral cranial nerve deficit + contralateral hemiparesis = brainstem lesion. This "crossed" pattern is PATHOGNOMONIC for brainstem stroke. If all deficits are on the same side, the lesion is above the brainstem (cortical or subcortical).')
